        },
        {
          "sn": "2.",
          "fields": [
            "(Optics)"
          ],
          "defs": [
            "A system of close equidistant parallel lines or bars, esp. lines ruled on a polished surface, used for producing spectra by diffraction; -- called also diffraction grating."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [
            "Gratings have been made with over 40,000 such lines to the inch, but those with a somewhat smaller number give the best definition. They are used, e. g., to produce monochromatic light for use in optical instruments such as spectrophotometers."
          ],
